\parai{Synthesis} references the ability to return individual results that integrate information from multiple sources (addressing what some refer to as ``global queries''). KGs and LLMs are capable of returning answers synthesized from multiple sources. While SEs index diverse sources, they cannot synthesize information to answer user queries; thus, if the information a user seeks is not provided in one document, the user must integrate and synthesize the relevant information manually from multiple sources.